<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for creating, editing and converting SmartArt diagrams in a PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to create SmartArt diagram in a PowerPoint presentation and convert it to PDF document.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Create and edit 134 default SmartArt diagram equivalent to Microsoft PowerPoint.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Add, modify and remove nodes of the SmartArt diagram.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Convert presentation with SmartArt diagram to PDF/Image.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph><Bold>Note:</Bold> This library supports creation, manipulation and conversion to PDF/image for .pptx format alone.</Paragraph>

